workflow SmokeScaffolding
  goal: "Smoke-test write_scaffolding_files end-to-end through tracker's Anthropic adapter. Uses claude-opus-4-6 as the outer agent (mirroring architect_only.dip's wire path) so we catch any tool_use serialization issues before re-running the full architect pipeline."
  start: Start
  exit: Exit

  defaults
    provider: anthropic

  tool Start
    label: "Start"
    timeout: 5s
    command:
      printf 'start'

  tool Exit
    label: "Exit"
    timeout: 5s
    command:
      printf 'exit'

  agent run_smoke
    label: "Smoke: call write_scaffolding_files once"
    model: claude-opus-4-6
    provider: anthropic
    max_turns: 4
    fallback_target: Exit
    prompt:
      You are running a smoke test for the `write_scaffolding_files` tool.

      Your job:

      1. Call `write_scaffolding_files` ONCE with no arguments. The tool reads
         `.ai/contract.md` and writes scaffolding files to their workspace-relative
         paths, then emits a manifest at `.ai/scaffolding_manifest.txt`.

      2. After the call returns, output the single word "done" on its own line and stop.

      Do NOT call any other tool. Do NOT inspect the files yourself. Do NOT call
      `write_scaffolding_files` more than once. Do NOT call `dispatch_sprints` —
      this is a tool-isolation smoke test, not a full architect run.

      ## Tool prerequisites
      `write_scaffolding_files` requires `TRACKER_SPRINT_WRITER_MODEL` env var
      set on the tracker process (e.g. `claude-sonnet-4-6`). The tool calls
      Sonnet internally to author the file set.

  edges
    Start -> run_smoke
    run_smoke -> Exit
